COMMENTS AND DOCUMENTATION
    Everything after a hash symbol '#' on given line is a comment.
    Everything after two hash symbols '##' on given line is a documentation.
    Documentation belongs to the subsequent language entity definition.

NAMES AND KEWORDS
    Upper-case words are reserved for keywords.
    Words with first capital character are reserved for type names.
    Other words can be used as names.

LANGUAGE ENTITIES
    Language entities are classes, functions, locations, properties, ...
    They are stored in a tree-like structure.
    You can use dot to access child entities of the parent entity.
    A chain of dot accesses is called a path.

FUNCTIONS
    Return value cannot be ignored silently.
    Return value can be ignored explicitly using VOID = call.
    Assignment operators has optional return value.